<subSubSection id="01A009D975458130FF20CEA6FB1BFD1B" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="49055A5275458130FF20CEA6FBC3FF66" blockId="21.[151,1437,151,642]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FF20CEA6FD95FF28" bold="true" box="[198,579,151,177]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution and phenology:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D175458130FDA2CEA9FCA8FF28" authorityName="Luteyn" authorityYear="2013" box="[580,894,152,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FDA2CEA9FCA8FF28" box="[580,894,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphyrospermum revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to eastern 
<collectingCountry id="31AD1AC275458130FB66CEA9FB37FF2B" box="[1152,1249,152,178]" name="Ecuador" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(Prov. Morona- Santiago), the “Oriente” region, and known only from the 
<typeStatus id="9601E4F075458130FCAECE8FFCACFF41" box="[840,890,190,216]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
collection which was flowering in November. It was collected in primary forest over sandstone substrate, at 
<quantity id="8E42F7B775458130FC8DCED4FBC7FF66" box="[875,1041,229,255]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.355" metricValueMax="1.3699999999999999" metricValueMin="1.34" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="1355.0" valueMax="1370.0" valueMin="1340.0">1340–1370 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49055A5275458130FF20CF3AFE9FFEEA" blockId="21.[151,1437,151,642]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FF20CF3AFE30FEBC" bold="true" box="[198,486,267,293]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="F9D2500F75458130FE03CF3DFE93FEEA" collectionCode="CR" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" specimenCode="B1" specimenCount="1">
The 
<typeStatus id="9601E4F075458130FDFDCF3DFD9BFEBF" box="[539,589,268,294]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
collection was made from the edge of a remnant forest in an area not so frequently collected by botanists, but deteriorated and with high logging activity. Critically endangered [
<collectionCode id="2FABC29775458130FA94CF03FA4DFED5" box="[1394,1435,306,332]" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
<specimenCode id="191CF22975458130FF71CF68FF63FEEA" box="[151,181,345,371]" collectionCode="CR" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="Herbarium">B1</specimenCode>
ab(i, iii, iv)]
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49055A5275458130FF20CF4EFB1BFD1B" blockId="21.[151,1437,151,642]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FF20CF4EFE45FE00" bold="true" box="[198,403,383,409]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Observations:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D175458130FE75CFB1FD03FE00" authorityName="Luteyn" authorityYear="2013" box="[403,725,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FE75CFB1FD03FE00" box="[403,725,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphyrospermum revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having revolute, slightly bullate and narrowly lanceolate leaves, flowers 5-merous with short-pilose pedicels and calyces, corollas that are glabrous and greenish-cream colored, and 10 stamens. 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D175458130FD26CFFCFBD4FE7F" authorityName="Luteyn" authorityYear="2013" box="[704,1026,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FD26CFFCFBD4FE7F" box="[704,1026,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphyrospermum revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D175458130FB45CFFCFA88FE7F" box="[1187,1374,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolium">
<emphasis id="7BCE864075458130FB45CFFCFA88FE7F" box="[1187,1374,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. linearifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NY isotype sterile) from 
<collectingCountry id="31AD1AC275458130FE76CFC5FDC7FD97" box="[400,529,500,526]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2D2B27A375458130FDC4CFC5FCB9FD97" author="Morales, J. F. &amp; Rodriguez, A." box="[546,879,500,526]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="335 - 337" refId="ref21303" refString="Morales, J. F. &amp; Rodriguez, A. (2005) Una nueva especie Sphyrospermum (Ericaceae) para Costa Rica. Novon 15: 335 - 337." type="journal article" year="2005">Morales &amp; Rodríguez 2005</bibRefCitation>
); the latter species differs by its more glabrous and non-lianoid habit, non-bullate leaves that are acute apically, much longer pedicels, smaller flowers with white corollas, and fewer stamens. Both species are known only from their 
<typeStatus id="9601E4F075458130FB84CC70FB4EFDC2" box="[1122,1176,577,603]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
specimens, so more collections are needed to evaluate the range of the characters and interspecific relationships.
</paragraph>
